---
By: William Hazlitt
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 71
    Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Contentment
---
When a man is contented with himself and his resources, all is well. When
he undertakes to play a part on the stage, and to persuade the world to
think more about him than they do themselves, he has gotten into a track
where he will find nothing but briars and thorns, vexation and
disappointment.
